This is the Openstack deployment demo folder.

Step 1: Run the script:
./openstack-prereqs-install.sh

Step 2: Change into a subdirectory of the deployment you want to use, use havana as default.
cd havana

Step 3: Run the pre-deployment to set up Juju and the GUI
./01demo-prep.sh

Step 4: Ready to run the demo!
./02deploy.sh

Step 5: Configure Openstack and Juju to Use Openstack
./03configure-cloud.sh

Step 6: Deploy other workloads ontop of Openstack.
See other demo workload folders

Step 7: Cleanup after a demo:
./04cleanup.sh

Ready to run the demo again.
